    base:desc "The Digital Twin synchronizes its internal state with the physical vehicle using a shared time base that achieves 100 ms absolute accuracy, as constrained by safety‑critical vehicular standards. Computation offloading between on‑board units depends on this coarse time alignment, enabling coordinated sensor fusion, vehicle‑to‑vehicle communication, and actuator command scheduling. All ROS2 nodes within the twin use the standard ROS time source, ensuring that timestamps on published messages and logged data are consistent across the distributed deployment."
