instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The overall orchestration follows the ISO 23247 Reference Architecture, mapping each Functional Element (FE) onto a ROS2 package that contains one or more ROS2 nodes. The system adopts an entity‑based structure: User Entity (visualization, control panel), Digital Twin Entity (data storage, control logic), and Physical Twin Entity (sensor/actuator handling, point‑cloud clustering, tracking). Resources such as compute nodes, sensors, and actuators are allocated per entity, enabling distributed processing across a vehicle’s network. ROS2 topics, services, and actions provide the intra‑system coordination mechanism, while the underlying middleware ensures message ordering, QoS, and fault tolerance. This constellation deviates from ISO 23247 by introducing a Physical Twin Entity that integrates general automotive functionality directly into the twin’s core resources."
]

